<concept id="concept_3413BBD173324104B42FB714974CABE7" xml:lang="en-us">
        <title>Defining Upgrade and Downgrade Options</title>
        <conbody>
                <section>
                        <p><ph
                                        conref="../../help/tasks/service_upgradeOptions.xml#task634/Upgrade_and_downgrade_options_task_taskbody_context_p_2_ph"
                                /></p>
                        <p>The following example shows upgrade options for a service on a marketplace:</p>
                        <fig>
                                <image align="center" height="250" href="../_images/MSUpgrade.png" placement="break"
                                        width="500"/>
                        </fig>
                        <p><ph
                                        conref="../../help/tasks/service_upgradeOptions.xml#task634/You_can_specify_any_number_of_task_taskbody_context_p_3_ph"
                                /></p>
                        <p
                                conref="../../help/tasks/service_upgradeOptions.xml#task634/When_a_customer_upgrades_or_d_task_taskbody_context_p_7"/>
                        <p
                                conref="../../help/tasks/service_upgradeOptions.xml#task634/When_a_customer_upgrades_or_d_task_taskbody_context_p_4"/>
                        <p
                                conref="../../help/tasks/service_upgradeOptions.xml#task634/The_prices_for_using_a_servic_task_taskbody_context_p_9"/>
                        <p>To define upgrade and downgrade options, use the <uicontrol>Define up/downgrade options</uicontrol> menu option in the <uicontrol>Marketable service</uicontrol> menu of the <ph
                                        conref="../../Shared/Product_Name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Abbr"
                                /> administration portal. </p>
                        <p>For defining upgrade and downgrade options, the relevant marketable services must be deactivated. As soon as you have published the services again, your customers can subscribe to them and are free to upgrade and downgrade their subscriptions as required.  </p>
                </section>
        </conbody>
</concept>
